{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbe69f1b-d0fb-46fa-a105-d53a74715a24","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. Update packages in your `.csproj`\n\n**Remove:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" />\n```\n\n**Update:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.0.0\" />\n```\n(v5+ supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively)\n\n### 2. Enable the new platform\n\nAdd to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Run tests\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **NUnit3TestAdapter 5.0+** is required — it ships a built-in Microsoft.Testing.Platform adapter, replacing the VSTest path.\n- `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` is **no longer needed** and should be removed to avoid conflicts.\n- The `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` property tells `dotnet test` to use the new platform instead of VSTest.\n- NUnit itself (the `NUnit` package) stays unchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"372e6178-fce5-43e6-a83e-90eb0c588e94","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":364,"requestId":"A02A:2C9D9E:BD1B41:DD5453:69FE855A"},"id":"06baaaba-5cf6-4e3d-82d4-bd24c794700e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:52:50.394Z","parentId":"743985e0-d07f-48fa-ab19-c7bf78c5c9b8"}
